14:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Feature Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Both Relume and Stencil share a solid foundation of core features including Templates, Drag And Drop, Export Formats. Where Relume pulls ahead is with exclusive access to Ai Generation and Collaboration and Responsive, which can be a deciding factor for teams that rely on these capabilities. On the other hand, Stencil uniquely offers Stock Assets, giving it an edge for users who prioritize this area. \n\nLooking at user ratings, Relume holds an overall score of 7/10 and an ease of use score of 7/10, while Stencil scores 5/10 overall and 9/10 for ease of use. These ratings reflect real user experiences and can indicate differences in usability, support quality, and overall satisfaction."}]]}]
15:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing Breakdown"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When it comes to pricing, both Relume and Stencil offer flexible pricing models. Both platforms offer free plans, which is great for testing before committing. Relume's free tier and Stencil's free tier each have their own limitations, so it is worth evaluating both to see which free offering better matches your initial needs."}]]}]
