18:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Relume is best suited for web designers, agencies, Webflow users, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Stencil, meanwhile, shines for social media managers, bloggers, quick image needs, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2022, Relume describes itself as \"AI website builder that generates sitemaps and wireframes from text prompts.\" Stencil, established in 2015, positions itself as \"Fast and simple image creation tool optimized for social media posts.\" With 7 years between them, Stencil brings the maturity and proven track record of a veteran platform, while Relume offers the fresh perspective and modern architecture of a newer entrant."}]]}]
19:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Relume** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (7.0 vs 5.0), more features (6 vs 4), availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean Stencil is a poor choice — far from it. Stencil excels in its own right, particularly for social media managers and bloggers.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value ai sitemap and wireframe generation, go with Relume. If extremely fast image creation matters more to you, Stencil is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
